st batch-to-batch difference table of standard seawater and its application to the WOCE onetime sections (2006) J. Oceanogr., 62, pp. 777-799; Levitus, S., Antonov, J.I., Boyer, T.P., Stephens, C., Warming of the world ocean (2000) Science, 287, pp. 2225-2229; Manabe, S., Stouffer, R.J., Spelman, M.J., Bryan, K., Transient responses of a coupled ocean-atmosphere model to gradual changes of atmospheric CO2. Part 1: Annual mean response (1991) J. Climate, 4, pp. 785-818; Orsi, A.H., Johnson, G.C., Bullister, J.B., Circulation, mixing and production of Antarctic Bottom Water (1999) Prog. Oceanogr., 43, pp. 55-109; Orsi, A.H., Smethie Jr., W.M., Bullister, J.L., On the total input of Antarctic waters to the deep ocean: A preliminary estimate from chlorofluorocarbon measurements (2002) J. Geophys. Res., 107, p. 3122; Peterson, B.J., McClelland, J., Curry, R., Holmes, R.M., Walsh, J.E., Aagaard, K., Trajectory shifts in the Arctic and Subarctic freshwater cycle (2006) Science, 313, pp. 1061-1066; Rahmstorf, S., Glacial climates: Thermohaline Circulation (2006) Encyclopedia of Quaternary Sciences, 1, pp. 739-750. , In ed. by S. A. Elias, Elsevier, Amsterdam; Rignot, E., Jacobs, S.S., Rapid bottom melting wide-spread near Antarctic ice sheet grounding lines (2002) Science, 296, pp. 2020-2023; Rintoul, S.R., On the origin and influence of Adélie Land Bottom Water, in Ocean, Ice, and Atmosphere: Interactions at the Antarctic Continental Margin (1998) Antarc. Res. Ser., 75, pp. 151-171. , In ed. by S. Jacobs and R. Weiss, American Geophysical Union, Washington, D.C; Rintoul, S.R., Rapid freshing of Antarctic Bottom Water formed in the Indian and Pacific oceans (2007) Geophys. Res. Lett., 34, pp. L06606; Shepherd, A., Wingham, D., Mansley, J., Rapid glacier thinning along the Amundsen Coast, West Antarctica (2001) Eos Trans. AGU, 82 (47), pp. F537; Shepherd, A., Wingham, D., Mansley, J., Corr, H., Inland thinning of Pine Island Glacier, West Antarctica (2001) Science, 291, pp. 